# The community engines' OWN source code is NOT vendored into this repo. Each is
# the property of its author under its own licence (Blackwood's solver is
# GPL-3.0; McGavin posted his C to the mailing list), and the per-author lab
# pages state plainly that the sources are "not copied here". Committing them
# would fold a GPL work into this MIT repo. So the whole engines/ tree is
# ignored: fetch the sources locally to rerun (run_community.sh documents where
# each comes from), exactly as the lab pages' repro commands describe.
#
# What IS committed is OUR method and results: the board parsers, run_community.sh,
# emit/build scripts, the rescored results-*.jsonl, and the unpinned instances.
engines/

# Run scratch and build artefacts.
.work/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
